@newbottega is bottling the scent of Italy once again. Expanding on its five-piece fragrance debut from 2024, the Italian fashion house has unveiled Alta, a new collection of ten eau de parfums that blend classic Italian aromas with unexpected notes sourced from around the world.⁠
⁠
Inspired by the brand’s signature intrecciato leather-weaving technique, each fragrance intertwines scents from different cultures, pairing elements such as blood orange from the gardens of Bottega’s Venetian atelier with North African neroli, or Italian bathing talc with Oceania sandalwood. The collection arrives in striking new bottles featuring woven-effect glass, finished with a gold ring and wooden cap, translating Bottega Veneta’s craftsmanship into fragrance form.⁠

