Let’s face it: the world is going to pieces. We’re living in the middle of an overwhelming 24x7 news cycle, a social media epidemic, global warming, megalomaniac leaders, and a looming AI revolution that poses a threat to job security, human rights, the environment, and integrity, among others. And through it all, we are told to practise mindfulness and gratitude. Be positive! See the silver lining! But how? When the future of our world seems so bleak, how does one really stay optimistic?
Deepika Chopra has the answer. Popularly known as the Optimism Doctor, California-based Chopra, a behavioural scientist, author, and podcast host with a doctorate in clinical health psychology, has just launched her first book, ‘The Power of Real Optimism’. A result of her work and personal lives converging, the book mirrors how we actually experience challenges and illustrates what real optimism is.
@priyankaskhanna in conversation with Chopra at the link in bio.

